main event: An unidentified observation reported on 7 May 1966 in Ridge, New York, which lacked sufficient data for evaluation.
interesting points: The report was part of Project Blue Book, which documented UFO sightings,The report concluded that there was insufficient data for evaluation,The witness was a 26-year-old waterfowl handler and a private pilot,The conditions were noted as clear to the north and hazy to the south,The report speculated that neon signs and search lights might have appeared as UFOs due to wind and cloud effects.
sighted object: a bright light in the night sky
